channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Chaos After Kamala's Detroit Rally Is Emblematic of What Her Presidency Would Do to America
Businesses, governments work to boost cyberdefense amid shortage in workers
item.description: U.S. government entities are devoting more time and resources to bolster cyberdefenses, including the Florida Center for Cybersecurity at the University of South Florida.

item.title: AP Poll: Americans See Democracy on Ballot but Differ on Threat
item.description: Roughly 3 in 4 American adults believe the upcoming presidential election is vital to the future of U.S. democracy, although which candidate they think poses the greater threat depends on their political leanings, according to a new poll.

item.title: Biden Now Trying to Stir Up Fear About What Would Happen After Election
Harris VP pick Tim Walz’s top five ‘weird’ moments in the spotlight
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate, Gov. Tim Walz, has hit the headlines for a number of comments he has made over his career and in recent days.

item.title: Rep. Self to Newsmax: 'Squad' Moved Dem Party to Communism
item.description: Rep. Keith Self, R-Texas, in a Newsmax appearance on Wednesday, said factions within the Democratic Party have moved it closer to communism.

item.title: Tim Walz Drove 95 in a 55, Tried to Flee Police, and Blamed It on 'Deafness'
Harris' VP pick faces backlash over resurfaced calls to transfer 'most dangerous terrorists' to US facilities
item.description: Gov. Tim Walz voted against a measure in 2009 that would have blocked the federal government from transferring inmates into the U.S. from Guantanamo Bay.

item.title: Marquette Wis. Poll: Trump-Harris in Dead Heat
item.description: A poll conducted by Marquette Law School that was released Wednesday shows Donald Trump at 50% and Kamala Harris at 49% in Wisconsin among registered voters, but Harris is at 50% and Trump at 49% among likely voters.

item.title: On Tim Walz, Stolen Valor, and American Values
Heritage chief mum on House Dems' demand for a meeting as left digs in on Project 2025
item.description: A group of House Democrats is demanding a sit-down with Heritage Foundation President Kevin Roberts as the left continues to use Project 2025 as a political cudgel.

item.title: Ronald Reagan Narrates Latest Trump Campaign Ad
item.description: The campaign for former President Donald Trump released a new one-minute commercial this week with narration from former President Ronald Reagan.

item.title: Kamala Harris Campaign Lures Rally Attendees a 2nd Time, With Free Concert in Wisconsin
'Never went to war': Walz ripped for saying he wants to ban guns he 'carried in war'
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz was ripped on social media after the Kamala Harris campaign published a video in which Walz said he wants to ban guns that he "carried in war."

item.title: US News: Republican Nassau County 'Safest' in America
item.description: Nassau County in New York is the safest county in America, according to a new survey from U.S. News and World Report.
